Package pfc.models

Show UML class diagram
Class Summary
Edge The Edge class represents the second of the two fundamental mathematical elements in a graph along with vertices.
Graph The Graph class represents the highest level data-structure in graph theory, containing—fundamentally and by definition—a list of vertices and a corresponding list of edges connecting those vertices.
ObservableList<T> An ObservableList is a collection which maintains an ordering for its elements.
ObservableModel The ObservableModel class is an extension of Observable, which provides a minimal implementation of the Observer pattern in Java.
Vertex The Vertex class represents one of the two fundamental mathematical elements in a graph along with edges.
